      • shortenBy

        public static Interval[] shortenBy(Interval interval,
                                   BigFraction fraction)
        Splits an interval into two by cutting off a portion. For example: if the original interval went from 0 to 1, and the fraction was 1/4, the new intervals would be [0, 3/4] and [3/4, 1].
        Parameters:
        interval - the original interval
        fraction - the amount by which to shorten
        Returns:
        an array of two intervals, long and short
